\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. P. padus} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 473 (1753) ({\i Cerasus padus} (L.) Delarbre). Tree or shrub with ascending branches; bark foetid. Leaves 6-10 cm, obovate to elliptic-oblong, acuminate, acutely and finely serrate, dull green above, paler beneath. Racemes with 15-35 flowers. Petals 6-9 mm, often  erose-denticulate. Fruit 6-8 mm, subglobose, shining black, bitter and astringent; endocarp sulcate. 2n = 32.{\i  Most of Europe except the Mediterranean region, Balkan peninsula and S.E. Russia.} Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Hb He Ho Hs It Ju Lu No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, K, E) Su.
